    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPa22">
<l>am kaṇ mā ñālattaracar apimāṉa</l>
<l>paṅkamāy vantu niṉ paḷḷik kaṭṭiṟ kīḻē</l>
<l>caṅkam iruppār pōl vantu talaippeytōm</l>
<l>kiṅkiṇi vāyc ceyta tāmaraip pūp pōlē</l>
<l>ceṅkaṇ ciṟuc ciṟitē yemmēl viḻiyāvō</l>
<l>tiṅkaḷum ātittiyaṉum eḻuntāṟ pōl</l>
<l>am kaṇ iraṇṭum koṇṭeṅkaḷ mēl nōkkutiyēl</l>
<l>eṅkaḷ mēl cāpam iḻintēlōr empāvāy</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Like the kings on the beautiful, spacious, big earth,</l>
<l>who, their haughtiness having been defeated,</l>
<l>come and gather together beneath Your throne,</l>
<l>We have come and approached [You].</l>
<l>Will the red eyes not open on us little by little</l>
<l>Like a lotus flower that resembles the opening of a small bell?</l>
<l>If You look at us with [Your] two beautiful eyes [that open]</l>
<l>like the moon and the sun rise,</l>
<l>The curses [that are] on us will come down.</l>
<l>O our maidens, accept [and] consider [this] attentively!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
